I wouldn't trade

00:54.355 --> 00:55.656
this experience for anything.

00:55.689 --> 00:58.292
- I feel the same way,
but what are we--

00:58.326 --> 00:59.793
- I'm not pulling out
my investment.

00:59.827 --> 01:01.262
You can breathe.
Okay.

01:01.295 --> 01:02.530
But I am making a change.

01:02.563 --> 01:05.199
An opportunity has
come up for me

01:05.233 --> 01:08.602
and I've decided to pursue
a senate bid.

01:08.636 --> 01:10.371
In California.

01:13.307 --> 01:15.143
- Wow.
- I know. Yeah.

01:15.176 --> 01:16.577
I'm still getting used
to saying it out loud.

01:16.610 --> 01:18.546
But I have been thinking
about it for a few years,

01:18.579 --> 01:21.249
and I've had a quiet exploratory
committee putting feelers out,

01:21.282 --> 01:24.218
and you know, the polls
look promising,

01:24.252 --> 01:26.854
so, it feels like
the right time.

01:26.887 --> 01:28.556
- My goodness.

01:28.589 --> 01:30.658
I mean, if anybody
can do this, it's you.

01:30.691 --> 01:33.727
- Thank you.
That means a lot.

01:36.197 --> 01:38.232
- * Whoa oh

01:38.266 --> 01:40.868
* She's the kind you'll
give your life for *

01:40.901 --> 01:43.571
