28:44.256 --> 28:46.058
That's true.

28:46.092 --> 28:47.293
- Oh my gosh.

28:47.326 --> 28:49.461
- Yeah, so one day I just like
completely had it with them,

28:49.495 --> 28:50.963
right, so I just started
coming back at them

28:50.997 --> 28:52.965
with whatever
I could think of.

28:52.999 --> 28:57.036
I told Jonah that his face

28:57.069 --> 28:59.839
looked like his butt threw up.

28:59.872 --> 29:01.140
- Wow.
- Yeah.

29:01.173 --> 29:03.075
So I'm thinking,
I'm such an idiot

29:03.109 --> 29:05.812
because I'm going to get
my ass kicked by these guys.

29:05.845 --> 29:07.914
But Jonah
just starts laughing.

29:07.947 --> 29:11.117
And he calls me over
to his lunch table,

29:11.150 --> 29:12.451
which was a big deal.
- Wow.

29:12.484 --> 29:15.888
- And yeah, we were
friends after that.

29:17.289 --> 29:18.791
Like, when he started
becoming famous.

29:18.825 --> 29:20.259
- Oh, my God,
that was so weird.

29:20.292 --> 29:22.962
It was like completely
bizarro alternate reality.

29:22.995 --> 29:25.164
It's like I can't believe
it's my life sometimes.

29:25.197 --> 29:26.565
It's crazy.
- I know what you mean.

29:26.598 --> 29:28.367
I mean, obviously,
not the same thing.

29:28.400 --> 29:30.069
- It's ridiculous.
- I know.

29:30.102 --> 29:31.203
- It is ridiculous.
- I know.

29:31.237 --> 29:33.372
- Yeah. I mean, people
treat Jonah

29:33.405 --> 29:35.174
like he's some kind
of god or something.

29:35.207 --> 29:39.011
He gets his nose hair trimmed,
and it's a national headline.

29:41.213 --> 29:43.049
Sorry. Sorry.

29:43.082 --> 29:44.283
I probably wasn't supposed
to tell you he has nose hair.

29:44.316 --> 29:45.985
That's my bad.

29:46.018 --> 29:47.019
Just keep that
between us, okay?

29:47.053 --> 29:48.955
- Just never speak of it again.

29:51.257 --> 29:52.859
- I'm good, thank you.
Okay.

29:52.892 --> 29:54.526
- I'm totally good.
- Let me know, though.

29:54.560 --> 29:55.928
- I'm good, thank you.
- Okay, I'm just doing my job.

29:55.962 --> 29:57.129
- Thank you.

30:13.612 --> 30:15.481
- Hm.

30:21.087 --> 30:22.521
Hey.

30:22.554 --> 30:24.323
- Hey, did I catch you
at a bad time?

30:24.356 --> 30:26.125
- No, no, I'm glad you called.
I--

30:26.158 --> 30:28.460
- I was wondering if you might
like to go out to dinner again.

30:28.494 --> 30:31.197
- Oh, wow.

30:31.230 --> 30:35.434
Sorry, I'm--I definitely
wasn't expecting that.

30:35.467 --> 30:37.336
Um, I've been thinking--

30:37.369 --> 30:39.338
- I promise it'll be
a much better dinner,

30:39.371 --> 30:40.940
and if it's about the--

30:40.973 --> 30:42.174
- Yeah, Deacon, I don't
want to come between

30:42.208 --> 30:43.409
you and your girls, you know.

30:43.442 --> 30:44.944
Especially not Daphne.

30:44.977 --> 30:46.412
I know she's in
a fragile place,

30:46.445 --> 30:49.015
and if this were to send her
into another depression,

30:49.048 --> 30:51.183
I just--I don't think
I could live with that. So--

30:51.217 --> 30:53.152
- I'm sorry this is all
so complicated.

30:53.185 --> 30:54.520
- No, no, it's not your fault.

30:54.553 --> 30:56.088
Really, it's mine.
It's just--

30:56.122 --> 30:57.924
- No, it's not your fault.

30:57.957 --> 31:00.092
- No, I think that
maybe it's better that we,

31:00.126 --> 31:03.095
um, just stop before--

31:03.129 --> 31:04.330
- Well, maybe we could--

31:04.363 --> 31:05.664
- You know, I have to get
off the phone actually.

31:05.697 --> 31:06.966
- Jessie, wait.

31:06.999 --> 31:08.267
- No, I'm--Jake just
walked in so,

31:08.300 --> 31:11.237
I'll call you later or--okay.
- Okay.

31:11.270 --> 31:12.404
- Bye.

31:19.078 --> 31:21.213
- I'm going to beat you.
- Oh, no, you're not.

31:21.247 --> 31:23.382
No, mm, mm, mm.

31:23.415 --> 31:25.217
- Hey.
Hey. Sorry.

31:25.251 --> 31:26.218
I had a thing
I couldn't get out of.

31:26.252 --> 31:27.653
- No worries.

31:27.686 --> 31:29.321
- So, uh, let's
play this back.

31:29.355 --> 31:31.123
Where's the guy?
- Yeah. Yeah, I'll get him.

31:34.526 --> 31:36.262
- Hey.

31:36.295 --> 31:38.998
- Yeah.

31:39.031 --> 31:41.567
- I'm sorry.
I don't think...

31:41.600 --> 31:44.070
I don't think
I can do this right now.

31:44.103 --> 31:46.638
I really like you,
but I don't think I can deal

31:46.672 --> 31:50.476
with everybody being
so involved in our business.

31:50.509 --> 31:53.145
You know, like I've had
people talk about me before,

31:53.179 --> 31:54.981
and it's never been good.

31:55.014 --> 31:57.649
- Look, look. I get it.
All right?

31:57.683 --> 32:00.086
Believe me, it's not
fun for me, either.

32:00.119 --> 32:03.255
You know, I just--I don't want
to be the guy who complains

32:03.289 --> 32:05.057
about how hard it is
to be famous, you know.

32:05.091 --> 32:06.425
I just--I don't know.

32:06.458 --> 32:09.595
I just try to look at it as
like that's the price

32:09.628 --> 32:12.198
for all the amazing things
in my life.

32:12.231 --> 32:15.001
Then I meet someone like you.

32:15.034 --> 32:17.369
And I just--I want
to get to know you

32:17.403 --> 32:19.171
without anyone watching.

32:19.205 --> 32:20.672
- I wish we could.

32:20.706 --> 32:23.609
- So then just
give me a chance.

32:23.642 --> 32:25.711
I'll find a way
to make it happen.

32:27.213 --> 32:30.116
- I have ideas.

32:35.254 --> 32:38.290
- Hey.
Did Cadence go down already?

32:38.324 --> 32:40.326
- Yeah. About an hour ago.

32:40.359 --> 32:42.294
- We had the most
incredible communal dinner.

32:42.328 --> 32:44.663
People just
told their stories.

32:44.696 --> 32:47.466
I had a long conversation
with Darius,

32:47.499 --> 32:50.469
and I think I can do this.

32:50.502 --> 32:53.005
I really think
I can make a change.

32:53.039 --> 32:56.275
- What kind of change
are we talking about?

32:56.308 --> 32:58.144
- Confronting my problems.

32:58.177 --> 32:59.278
On a deep level.

32:59.311 --> 33:03.349
So I can be a better partner,
I can be a better mom.

33:03.382 --> 33:06.718
I've really been trying.
- I know.

33:06.752 --> 33:12.091
And I see how hard
you're working on yourself,

33:12.124 --> 33:15.261
and I'm really proud
of you for that. I am.

33:16.362 --> 33:18.730
You need me to do it your way?

33:18.764 --> 33:21.267
Go back to rehab because
let me--let me tell ya,

33:21.300 --> 33:22.734
it did not work.

33:22.768 --> 33:24.270
- I'm not--I'm not saying
you have to do it my way.

33:24.303 --> 33:27.206
But it's just you're--

33:27.239 --> 33:30.542
you're putting all of
your trust into this guy.

33:30.576 --> 33:32.211
You're spending all
of your time there,

33:32.244 --> 33:34.546
you're living your
whole life by his words.

33:34.580 --> 33:37.083
- Did you even give
him a chance?

33:37.116 --> 33:38.450
Or did you just decide
this was wrong

33:38.484 --> 33:40.086
because you
don't understand it?

33:40.119 --> 33:43.255
- I've done nothing
but give this a chance.

33:43.289 --> 33:45.824
I've bitten my tongue every time
I got a weird vibe off of him.

33:45.857 --> 33:48.694
I mean, that's how bad
I want to support you.

33:48.727 --> 33:51.197
- Oh, honey, you can
say you support me

33:51.230 --> 33:53.799
until the cows come home,
but I feel it when you don't.

33:53.832 --> 33:56.402
I don't know if
this is because

33:56.435 --> 33:58.237
you feel threatened by him

33:58.270 --> 34:01.607
or maybe you're just
so used to me leaning on you.

34:01.640 --> 34:03.542
- You seriously
think that's why?

34:06.312 --> 34:09.115
- Just think what you want.

34:09.148 --> 34:10.549
You will anyway.

34:12.351 --> 34:14.386
- To bed.

34:30.402 --> 34:32.438
- Laura and the other
folks are volunteering

34:32.471 --> 34:34.173
at the building site again.

34:34.206 --> 34:37.676
And if you have a problem
with me going, that is fine.

34:37.709 --> 34:40.546
Okay?
Honor your feelings.

34:40.579 --> 34:42.448
But I'm going.

34:42.481 --> 34:43.849
I'll be back tonight.

34:43.882 --> 34:46.418
Maybe then you'll be
less mad at me.

34:49.655 --> 34:51.690
I'm just worried about you.

34:51.723 --> 34:53.259
- Don't be.

